title: For Sale:  Finnish P-27 Mosin Nagant Extremely Rare Variation 1897 Sestroryetsk Receiver 7.62x54r
postcontent:
For sale or trade is a P-27 Finnish Mosin Nagant built on an 1897 Sestroryetsk receiver. This is considered the "Holy Grail" of Mosin Nagants as only 8,000-12,000 P series rifles were made. Since this is also made using an 1897 Sestroryetsk receiver, it adds a level of extreme rarity on top!  The "Salerno Method" barrel has good rifling and this is a functioning rifle, so it will shoot.  I single loaded about 20 rds through her when I first got the rifle, cleaned it and put her away.  The stock shows all the character that an old war horse should, while still remaining very nice.  It has an interesting 'splice' in it (see pics).  I have many additional pictures if you are interested.  Rifle is import marked, and it has all the correct Finn markings and is a forced matched rifle.  This is as good as it gets for Mosins! 

I am open to all trades, both down and up, although I prefer cash.  I am also open to all fair offers so please don't hesitate to ask.  Out of state buyers are fine, and upon payment clearance, I will ship to your FFL for $35.

Items that I am willing to trade for include: modern and antique firearms, ammunition (most popular calibers),  ak's and ar's, archery items, antique swords / bayonets / military items, etc.

title: For Sale:  Arsenal SLR 107 FR, side folding polymer 7.62 x 39 AK 47 variant
postcontent:
Up for sale is a used but not abused SLR 107 FR (yes the older designation rifle, this is not not the newer 107-21 etc)

These Bulgarian Arsenal rifles have the distinction of being assembled overseas at the Bulgarian factory in Arsenal by their own technicians. The rifles are then imported here and have the furniture and trigger assemblies swapped out along with muzzle attachments to become 922r compliant. But the finish and assembly of the rifle is all factory done in Bulgaria. 

I do not know if this is still the practice today as I have been out of the AK scene for a while, but was still the practice when this rifle was made.

Less than 500 rounds through the rifle.
Some finish wear visible on the receiver, but nothing has gone through to the metal. 
Stock is firm and locks solid, (not that I have ever seen one come loose)
Missing the muzzle attachment, but is threaded to accept one. 
Acquired it a while back, but never used or fired it.

ONLY TRADES I WILL CONSIDER: 1911 WWII or WWI era, excellent condition Bulgarian or Russian military Makarov, quality AK variants, Excellent condition Remington Model 14 and model 8 in 35 Remington.

Up for sale or trade is a 100 percent spec SDM-R AR15 Compitiion gun. Gun was assembled by Compass Lake engineering the same company that built the barrels as well as some of the Armys SDM-r Rifles. This is a sub moa gun ready for comps etc. Built to spec true sdm-r rifle

Details:
CLE (Compass lake) 1/8 twist match chambered 20 inch barrel with 12 deep flutes under handguard. (shoots 5.56 or 223)
Colt upper and Bolt carrier
Daniel Defense m412 rail
Bolt matched to barrel
4 set screw adjustable FSB
Vortex flash hider
Knights Armament 2 stage match trigger
Armalite lower receiver
A2 stock
Matech Rear BUIS
Eagle sling with magpul front QD

Link:http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Army_Squad_Designated_Marksman_Rifle
Upper and lower receivers: The rifles were produced by the Army Marksmanship Unit (AMU) at Fort Benning, Georgia using either new semi-automatic ArmaLite lower receivers or existing Army M16A2 or A4 lower receivers previously supplied by either Colt or Fabrique Nationale de Herstal. All rifles were equipped with a fixed A2 stock and a Knight's Armament Company 2-stage match grade trigger capable of only semi-automatic fire. The upper receivers were flat-top style, but unlike the SAM-R and SPR, they did not have extended feed ramps.
Barrel: The 1:7 twist, 20-inch (510 mm) barrel from the M16A2 and A4 were replaced with a stainless steel Douglas Barrels 1:8 twist, 20-inch barrel, with 12 flutes cut into the barrel to reduce weight. The front sight block was installed with 4 set screws instead of two taper pins. The SDM-R retained the A2-style flash hider.
Sights and optics: The issued optic was a 4x32 Advanced Combat Optical Gunsight (ACOG) (models TA31F, TA31RCO, TA01, TA01B, or TA01NSN). A Matech Industries 600-meter backup iron sight was also used.
Handguard: Daniel Defense M4 Rail 12.0 handguard, with an octagonal aluminum collar locking it to the upper receiver. The handguard provides a free-floating Picatinny rail forend.
Bipod: A Harris S-L bipod attached to an ARMS #17 throw-lever rail mount was mounted to the underside of the handguard. Since the handguard was free-floating, it did not come into contact with the barrel, and any pressure from the bipod on the handguard did not deflect the barrel.

title: For Sale:  Ultimate Tactical Load Out Survival Vest Rig
postcontent: I am marketing an Ultimate Tactical Load Out Survival Vest Rig. Everyone is selling load out bags and backpacks but this is a vest with drop leg attachments that will hold all your gear and supplies. Let's face it, when SHTF and in the worse case scenario you will only be able to take what you can carry. My rig offers the ability to carry all you gear and supplies in a one piece rig consisting of a tactical vest and drop leg attachments. You can still add a backpack to this configuration for even more cargo capability, but this configuration offers a load distribution that can be used as a stand alone option. Just grab and throw on and you are ready for whatever is thrown your way as long as you are properly prepared (I.E. survival skills, proper prep & supplies). In my experience it has always been a mobility issue in most survival situations. You can't take a department store or hospital with you when it is time to depart to safer or more secure area and you may not always be able to use transportation other than your own two feet. I will be posting detailed photos of this rig soon and am only posting this now to give people a heads up. I will offer the vest rig empty for $300. I will stock a vest per order depending on what a customer needs. This way if you have existing gear you would like to use, you can and just supplement what you don't. What I will offer will be a comprehensive First Aid Kit, Survival kit, Hydration  / Purification System and Shelter System that will be incorporated into the vest rig. Here are 8 sealed 72 round boxes of Romanian Military 7.62x25 ammunition.

This ammo is loaded in clean brass cases and has a FMJ bullet. The bullet jacket is a two part deal with a thicker steel inner jacket covered by a thin copper outer jacket. The bullet does attract a magnet because of the heavy steel inner jacket. Ammo is 100% surefire. It is corrosive primed so simply clean your gun after shooting and you will never have any issues.

I have not opened the 8 boxes that are for sale here, but similar ammo from open boxes had more recent production dates that were in the late 70's and early 80's while most of the other surplus 7.62 TOK ammo on the market today is from the 50's and 60's.
